<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_4f6ddac7-c14b-4629-8bc3-9383a75bb251" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>13.7.5</sptc><title id="_19eda7b5-c9bf-455e-95f9-3c3044f8012a">Electric resistance space heating</title><archive-num>2019: 3.12.5.4</archive-num><subclause id="_735bb960-5a01-4f75-8158-c7e5cf6469a3" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_679333b7-3192-46ff-a651-28be61e8a448">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>An electric resistance space heating system that serves more than one room must have—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_0817e685-c2d7-408b-a4df-ae48c334c230">separate isolating switches for each room; and</li><li id="_498a8be5-8aee-4183-b62f-b796878c1891">a separate temperature controller and time switch for each group of rooms with common heating needs; and</li><li id="_8f3a571c-8462-4819-a12a-ada1ffb28ee2">power loads of not more than 110 W/m<sup xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_62485858-3f89-4fa1-9ff7-ee1952c107f7" inv:access="external">2</sup> for living areas, and 150 W/m<sup xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_5c6cdc85-5bb1-4e05-b4c4-a926888bf308" inv:access="external">2</sup> for bathrooms.</li></ol></subclause></clause>